Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.77,0:00:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hint to reasoning is to dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.56,0:00:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a mystery behind every case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.69,0:00:08.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Four cute little pet dogs,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.52,0:00:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the four suspicious breeders.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.07,0:00:11.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeking the one and only truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.90,0:00:13.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.49,0:00:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is... Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.12,0:01:47.79,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,The Evidence That Didn't Disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.12,0:01:47.79,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,(Part 1)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.79,0:01:50.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.05,0:01:55.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a male Shiba Inu, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.80,0:01:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.01,0:02:02.85,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Teruya Kanou (26)\NProfessor Agasa's Friend's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.05,0:01:59.55,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.55,0:02:04.64,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You know, from the creator of the famous\NDetective Holmes: Arthur Conan Doyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.47,0:02:08.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, if he partners up with Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.06,0:02:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They would be the best detective team, wouldn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.48,0:02:12.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, are you comparing me to a dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.98,0:02:14.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.19,0:02:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that's a cute, girlish idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.53,0:02:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've said too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.70,0:02:20.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.87,0:02:25.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, the town has sure changed over the past ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.83,0:02:28.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, were you able to find the new parking lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.37,0:02:32.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The entrance there is quite hard to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.17,0:02:35.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} helped me read the map, so we found it just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.14,0:02:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Arthur! Will you stop that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.18,0:02:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.06,0:02:49.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's never been agitated enough to bark like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.85,0:02:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.06,0:02:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By chance, before you got here, did you\Ncome into contact with another dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.57,0:02:58.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, a bigger male breed than this Shiba Inu?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.78,0:03:05.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and I pet a Doberman that a friend in the\Nneighborhood brought to my house this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.87,0:03:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.95,0:03:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's some fur on your pants.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.46,0:03:14.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dogs can figure out the size and\Nsex of the dog from its scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.34,0:03:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he caught the scent of a larger male dog on you,\Nhe saw you as an enemy and became aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.42,0:03:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, you and Haibara were at this entrance once, but\Nleft when Kanou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} asked you to park the car, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.89,0:03:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arthur got the impression that you were turned away by his\Nmaster, but came back again as his master's enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.24,0:03:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.36,0:03:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're really stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.45,0:03:46.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess he and Conan may have a little bit\Nof the same thoughtless personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.20,0:03:48.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.12,0:03:53.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be hard on him, that was just an instinctive mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.46,0:03:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dangerous person who is not his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.50,0:03:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In my case,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.38,0:04:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he may not have been mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.97,0:04:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.01,0:04:06.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.26,0:04:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.85,0:04:16.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's another reason why Arthur kept barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.94,0:04:23.20,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Your voice wasn't firm enough when you commanded him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.48,0:04:27.45,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Yoshio Tsunashima (45)\NDog Breeder
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.20,0:04:26.49,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If your voice isn't firm when commanding him,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.49,0:04:31.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He'll think he's doing the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.75,0:04:33.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pay attention to that next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.33,0:04:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.21,0:04:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.67,0:04:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Tsunashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. I met him\Nat the Dog Breeders' Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.17,0:04:42.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He came here for the same reason you did, Agasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.51,0:04:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.80,0:04:49.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cool! I'll take this plane!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:51.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take this doll!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.81,0:04:55.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for me, I'll be taking this antique hourglass.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.52,0:04:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this really okay? These things look very expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.65,0:04:59.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.65,0:05:03.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My late grandfather bought and gathered these\Nthings as a hobby during his travels abroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.45,0:05:07.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The three of us in the family don't really\Nhave any interest in those antiques.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.78,0:05:10.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Selling them would be disrespectful to my grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.41,0:05:13.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So my father and mother decided to\Ngive them to our acquaintances.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.79,0:05:17.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of your parents, where are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.29,0:05:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My parents have been getting ready since\Nyesterday to move into their new house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.92,0:05:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since my job is forcing me to move to England,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.30,0:05:30.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and due to their old age, they decided to\Nmove to the countryside, near my uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why we're giving away everything inside this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.48,0:05:41.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, Arthur is the only thing\NI'm bringing with me to England.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My parents will be taking my mother's dog, Doyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.78,0:05:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a Papillon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:53.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you have one named Arthur and another one\Nnamed Doyle, is there one named Conan too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.29,0:05:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Shepherd my father used to have was named Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.33,0:05:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, he died two years ago due to an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.25,0:06:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.67,0:06:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's all right, we'll always have you Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.84,0:06:07.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.34,0:06:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't Papillon a weird name for a kind of dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.89,0:06:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Papillon means "butterfly" in French.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:18.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were very popular in the 16th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.39,0:06:22.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even Queen Marie Antoinette owned a Papillon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:27.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But whenever I see this dog, I'm still amazed by his fur!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.61,0:06:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No wonder he had a crushing victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.49,0:06:33.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crushing victory?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.03,0:06:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In those competitions that my mother\Nsometimes entered him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.99,0:06:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he's such a fine dog that people even\Noffered one million yen to buy him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.33,0:06:43.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One million!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.04,0:06:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Truly,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.13,0:06:46.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a valuable, elegant dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.17,0:06:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he's exactly like that selfish, spoiled\NFrench queen who was decapitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.01,0:06:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tosabayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.18,0:06:58.98,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Aki Tosabayashi (39)\NDog Breeder
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.18,0:06:59.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The door was open, so I took the liberty of entering.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.73,0:07:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your mother told me that she'll give me whatever I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.06,0:07:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at the moment, I have no interest\Nin anything except this big vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.03,0:07:11.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides that, everyone can take whatever they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.95,0:07:14.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I'll just be taking what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.91,0:07:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is she a fellow dog breeder too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.24,0:07:20.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she wasn't always like that, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.79,0:07:26.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's still mad that her dog lost against\NDoyle in the competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.38,0:07:32.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no! She might take the clock that\NI claimed in the Japanese room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.89,0:07:35.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should put a note on it so nobody takes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.60,0:07:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, why don't you choose something too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.81,0:07:42.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't get an opportunity like this every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.56,0:07:44.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are many cool things here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.86,0:07:46.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.57,0:07:50.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, I think I'll take this dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.24,0:07:57.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'm killed like Marie was, and when\Nthe dew on the guillotine vanishes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.45,0:08:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he will drown himself in the Seine river, like Marie's\Ndog Thisbe did, following me in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.75,0:08:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.71,0:08:10.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-She's an unusual girl, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.55,0:08:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhhh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.26,0:08:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.68,0:08:16.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try to lift her spirits a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.05,0:08:23.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's serious. She hasn't left the house since the bus incident,\Nand I was barely able to convince her to come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.27,0:08:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.85,0:08:30.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the incident, I asked Inspector Takagi if\Nthere were any suspicious people on the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.44,0:08:34.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said that there weren't any unidentifiable\Npeople and there's no reason to be worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.49,0:08:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did tell her this on the phone though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.37,0:08:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that fear is not normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.70,0:08:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's not eating at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and she has trouble sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.88,0:08:54.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, all I can say now is that even if there was\Na member of the Black Organization on that bus,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.97,0:08:59.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they shouldn't be aware of Haibara's existence yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.64,0:09:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been ten days since that incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.22,0:09:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they had figured it out, we would be dead by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both of us, you, and the three of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.81,0:09:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case... Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.90,0:09:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey. Not again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.07,0:09:19.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um... Agasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please don't be shy, help yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.99,0:09:21.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.91,0:09:23.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.37,0:09:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! If that's the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.00,0:09:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I'll take this stereo over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.83,0:09:30.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.13,0:09:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone's already reserved that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.05,0:09:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arthur, don't do that. You're not supposed\Nto come in here with muddy feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.10,0:09:41.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.47,0:09:42.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Arthur?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.56,0:09:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.85,0:09:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand, so let me go Arthur! Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.06,0:09:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you want to show me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.19,0:09:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.61,0:09:57.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I pressed the doorbell several times,\Nbut it seems to be broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.28,0:10:00.70,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Shino Hasuki (27)\NDog Breeder
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.28,0:10:00.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Arthur was thoughtful enough to bring you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.57,0:10:02.95,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,So, please don't be mad at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.95,0:10:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's my fault for not noticing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.41,0:10:08.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, go play with Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.50,0:10:15.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They seem to get along really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.30,0:10:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's a Shetland Shepherd, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:19.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, her name is Christie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:21.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.55,0:10:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The king and queen of mystery novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.89,0:10:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could she be the one who reserved the stereo?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.10,0:10:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.14,0:10:32.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought it would be a great present to celebrate\Nmy brother's admission into Senior High School.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.52,0:10:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't really care, but wouldn't it be better\Nto separate those two dogs quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.24,0:10:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they were to mate, their offspring would\Nbe a worthless mix that wouldn't sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.03,0:10:44.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.20,0:10:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arthur will be leaving for England soon anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Kanou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.80,0:10:58.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with Doyle?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.84,0:11:00.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's time for his snack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.89,0:11:05.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My grandfather loved dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.60,0:11:06.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So my mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.97,0:11:13.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,gave Doyle his snacks in front of the Buddhist altar in the\NJapanese room, so my late grandfather could see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.77,0:11:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Doyle eventually formed a habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.15,0:11:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he hears the clock chime at noon, he\Nwould go directly to the Japanese room,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.03,0:11:25.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and sit on a flat cushion to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.95,0:11:28.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Flat cushion?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.70,0:11:31.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Doyle adores the blue flat cushion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.92,0:11:35.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He even brings it in front of the Buddhist altar himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.29,0:11:39.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But doesn't the clock sound the same at midnight?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.55,0:11:42.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happens if Doyle mistakes that for noon?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.63,0:11:44.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.01,0:11:48.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We asked the clockmaker to set it\Nto chime only at 12 o'clock noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.60,0:11:53.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is it okay for me to take such a precious clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.31,0:12:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. My mother decided to stop spoiling him and feed\Nhim only twice a day, in the morning and night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.11,0:12:01.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's fine then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.11,0:12:02.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.86,0:12:04.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a peek through the gap.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.66,0:12:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doyle is sitting, right? On his favorite blue cushion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.25,0:12:12.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.25,0:12:15.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The blue cushion hasn't been removed either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.09,0:12:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that he didn't see the blue cushion\Nbecause it was placed under a brown one?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.63,0:12:30.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. He usually removes it to sit on even\Nif there are other cushions on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.93,0:12:32.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.10,0:12:33.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.77,0:12:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, let's split up and look for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.77,0:12:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be terrible if he went to\Na strange place and got stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.40,0:12:43.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doyle!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.11,0:12:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.24,0:12:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on out, Doyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.95,0:12:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doyle!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.99,0:12:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't find him anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.21,0:12:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, did you find him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:12:55.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we haven't found him yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.87,0:12:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We looked everywhere, even in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.71,0:13:00.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's Arthur's bark.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.17,0:13:03.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Christie's as well. They're barking together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.67,0:13:05.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's coming from the backyard. Let's go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.52,0:13:14.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's smoke coming out of the incinerator!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.23,0:13:16.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That incinerator...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.85,0:13:18.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't used it in years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.23,0:13:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.78,0:13:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.24,0:13:32.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be! It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.79,0:13:36.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dog collar!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.12,0:13:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.46,0:13:41.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doyle's?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.30,0:13:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a lie... It's a lie...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.56,0:14:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doyle! Doyle! Doyle! Doyle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.52,0:14:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.99,0:14:08.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing burnt is this collar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.20,0:14:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no dog corpse inside the incinerator.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.20,0:14:14.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, does this really belong to Doyle?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.12,0:14:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't see him wearing it earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.62,0:14:16.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.87,0:14:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usually we can't see it because it's hidden under his fur.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.92,0:14:22.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though it's burnt, there's no\Nmistaking its color and shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.17,0:14:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a very old collar that my grandfather bought\Nspecially from France for his Papillon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.80,0:14:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, come here for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.80,0:14:34.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The back door is unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.27,0:14:37.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.35,0:14:38.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.77,0:14:43.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit who kidnapped Doyle must\Nhave escaped through this back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.77,0:14:45.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.65,0:14:48.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did he burn the collar?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.86,0:14:53.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably because without his collar, we won't\Nbe able to identify him from other Papillons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.20,0:14:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since a collar with such decorations would be unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.58,0:14:58.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.79,0:15:02.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because after kidnapping the dog,\Nthe culprit had to run away quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.29,0:15:09.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't have bothered to burn a collar that's usually\Nhidden, and reveal his escape route, would he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.59,0:15:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably wants us to believe that he left the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.85,0:15:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Doyle is still...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.89,0:15:16.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.72,0:15:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a large possibility that he's hidden\Nsomewhere inside this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.81,0:15:23.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.11,0:15:28.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that the culprit is still among us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.28,0:15:32.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey. Don't tell me you're suspecting us now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.82,0:15:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not really. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.12,0:15:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it's as the boy says, then it's\Nobvious who the culprit is, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:41.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, please look.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.58,0:15:44.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those feminine shoes there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.09,0:15:47.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are mine, but how?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.05,0:15:49.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, feigning ignorance are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.80,0:15:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't you the one who brought\Nthem here from the entrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.68,0:15:54.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.01,0:15:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.85,0:15:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit wouldn't have left their shoes behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.56,0:16:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, it would have been suspicious if she was\Ncarrying the shoes under her arms in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.65,0:16:07.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't Hasuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s first nor second visit here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.90,0:16:10.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.03,0:16:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it would have been easy for you to train Christie\Nto bring your shoes from the entrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.32,0:16:20.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and also to return them back there, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.45,0:16:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.21,0:16:26.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, why don't we search for Doyle again?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.17,0:16:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We children will search with Onii{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.\NProfessor, please search with the three of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.09,0:16:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ye-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.81,0:16:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But where do we search, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.39,0:16:45.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We searched almost the entire house earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.35,0:16:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this time, we won't search for places dogs might\Nhide, but places where humans would hide one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.36,0:16:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Arthur can help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.78,0:16:59.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious? We can use his sense of smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.66,0:17:03.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dog's nose is its most powerful weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.79,0:17:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dog's nose is much more sensitive than a human's.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.75,0:17:13.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, if we give Arthur the missing Doyle's\Nscent, he'll surely find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.05,0:17:16.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, I brought it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.80,0:17:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the cushion Doyle usually sleeps on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.18,0:17:20.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go, smell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.93,0:17:25.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that might work if it's a police dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not really, this might actually work. My\Nfather always teased him like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.53,0:17:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems like he's picked up something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.57,0:17:40.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's entering the Japanese room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.58,0:17:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, maybe Doyle's in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.79,0:17:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A blue cushion?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.88,0:17:53.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, Doyle likes the blue cushion, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.46,0:17:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do dogs like the color blue?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.34,0:18:04.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's weird. I remember that there\Nwere only two blue cushions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.35,0:18:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now there are three, including the one Arthur found.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.11,0:18:12.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One extra?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.65,0:18:15.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.15,0:18:19.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, it's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.16,0:18:25.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, did Arthur ever hide shoes as a prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.58,0:18:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, but rather the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.25,0:18:34.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a story from when Arthur was still a puppy. Whenever\NI stood up, he thought we were going for a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.59,0:18:40.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would rush to the entrance before me, take\Nmy shoes out from the shoe rack, and wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.72,0:18:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now he understands that it's not\Nalways for a walk, so he stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.85,0:18:47.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.43,0:18:50.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arthur is definitely more than just a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.81,0:18:54.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, why don't you track Doyle's scent once more?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.61,0:18:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like he found something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.78,0:19:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he stopped in front of the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.49,0:19:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seems to be thinking about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.75,0:19:10.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, he resumed his walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.29,0:19:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's heading towards the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.46,0:19:16.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's gone outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.42,0:19:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That must mean that Doyle has been taken outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.89,0:19:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, he's just flirting with Christie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.60,0:19:30.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have been bored of searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.39,0:19:31.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't do anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.23,0:19:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is there anywhere Doyle hides whenever\Nsomeone gets angry at him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.11,0:19:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be possible that he went to hide after he\Nwas shocked by the culprit taking his collar off?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.99,0:19:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arthur used to hide under my bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.20,0:19:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Under your bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.12,0:19:51.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.96,0:19:55.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we first brought Doyle home, Arthur often got scolded.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.92,0:20:03.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whenever we cuddled the puppy Doyle, Arthur would\Nget jealous and tear the cushions to bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.18,0:20:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now they've become best friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.64,0:20:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Poor thing. Maybe Doyle is hiding\Nsomewhere, shivering in fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.90,0:20:14.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.48,0:20:19.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Worried about being discovered, living in fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.65,0:20:21.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a painful thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.07,0:20:24.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, cut it out. Are you sulking?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.82,0:20:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.20,0:20:31.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm telling them about the dangerous situation\Nof an optimist without a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.75,0:20:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know the reason but,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.08,0:20:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that one of their men was with us on the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.09,0:20:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they noticed my true identity at that time, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.80,0:20:45.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you and I,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.01,0:20:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And everyone will...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.72,0:20:48.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.60,0:20:51.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your true identity will never be revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.27,0:20:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why? How can you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.52,0:20:59.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you can sniff out their scent,\NI can also recognize them...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.57,0:21:04.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From their blood-thirsty presence,\Nthrough my detective instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.65,0:21:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it wasn't very hard once I knew\Nthe owner of this presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.58,0:21:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the very least, there wasn't anyone on that bus.\NThe one who thirsts for your blood wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.08,0:21:18.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with that look?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.54,0:21:20.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you making fun of a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.17,0:21:23.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not at all. I'm just amazed that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.01,0:21:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.01,0:21:30.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, let's recall today's events\Nwhen Doyle went missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.22,0:21:35.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the clock chimed at noon,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.77,0:21:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doyle ran to the Japanese room where he gets\Nhis snack, disappearing from our sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.82,0:21:46.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we followed Kanou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to the kitchen,\Nwhere he prepared the plate of cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.82,0:21:51.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, we went to the Japanese room\Nand realized Doyle wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.70,0:21:54.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, everyone split up to search the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.71,0:21:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a diagram of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.83,0:22:00.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know who searched where...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.17,0:22:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where exactly did the culprit hide him?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.72,0:22:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, how is he planning to get Doyle out of here?
